					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7415347#post-3963294</guid>
				<title>Re: #Team Sugary Sweet</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7415347/scp-3744#post-3963294</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 09 Sep 2018 03:57:40 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>keyii</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4420424</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Hello! I'm Keyii &#8212; Jan contacted me about doing a collaboration after deciding that he disliked the previous SCP-3744. This is the third work that I've had a hand in on this site, following <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-3009">SCP-3009</a> and its accompanying tale, <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/grin-and-bear-it">Grin and Bear It</a>.</p> <p>My part in the collab was mostly regarding characterization in the interview and a complete rehaul of the session log. It is now very different from its original incarnation, and hopefully in a good way! Thank you so much to everyone who critiqued this in chat, and I hope you enjoyed reading this.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
